1
00:01:33,896 --> 00:01:37,979
INDIAN AIRLINES

2
00:02:42,021 --> 00:02:43,479
I've tried everything I could.

3
00:02:44,146 --> 00:02:45,312
PM's under immense pressure.

4
00:02:46,812 --> 00:02:49,312
ISI has fed the international
media the story

5
00:02:50,062 --> 00:02:52,771
that our negotiations
have completely failed.

6
00:02:53,937 --> 00:02:55,354
And the terrorists could,
at any moment,

7
00:02:56,021 --> 00:02:57,896
kill the passengers sitting on that plane.

8
00:02:58,354 --> 00:03:00,062
Sir, you know that's not true.

9
00:03:02,479 --> 00:03:04,021
These bastards are about to break.

10
00:03:05,229 --> 00:03:06,520
From asking for 36 terrorists
to be released,

11
00:03:06,521 --> 00:03:08,021
they've now come down to just three.

12
00:03:08,812 --> 00:03:10,061
Sir, give me a little more time,

13
00:03:10,062 --> 00:03:12,312
and I promise you we won't have
to release a single terrorist...

14
00:03:12,687 --> 00:03:15,687
and we'll get every passenger
back home safe and sound.

15
00:03:15,854 --> 00:03:17,437
It's just a question of time.

16
00:03:18,937 --> 00:03:21,270
For the past three days,
the hostages' families

17
00:03:21,271 --> 00:03:23,771
have been protesting
outside the PM residence.

18
00:03:26,437 --> 00:03:27,771
Unfortunately, this is it.

19
00:03:50,021 --> 00:03:51,062
Come on...

20
00:03:51,229 --> 00:03:52,270
Get out of here!

21
00:03:52,271 --> 00:03:54,396
- Get him!
- Grab the bastard.

22
00:04:00,979 --> 00:04:02,646
Thrash him!

23
00:04:09,396 --> 00:04:11,396
Slit his throat.

24
00:04:11,771 --> 00:04:12,811
Get up.

25
00:04:12,812 --> 00:04:14,145
Slit his throat.

26
00:04:14,146 --> 00:04:15,271
Hold him down.

27
00:04:47,687 --> 00:04:51,812
Zahoor, we won't negotiate at gunpoint.

28
00:05:05,521 --> 00:05:06,437
So, what have you guys decided?

29
00:05:07,104 --> 00:05:08,646
We have conferred with our Prime Minister.

30
00:05:09,312 --> 00:05:11,771
Tomorrow, all three of them...
Mushtaq Ahmed Zargar,

31
00:05:12,646 --> 00:05:13,728
Ahmed Omar Saeed Sheikh,

32
00:05:13,729 --> 00:05:15,521
and your brother,
Maulana Masood Azhar,

33
00:05:16,479 --> 00:05:19,354
will be released from prison
and handed over to you here in Kandahar.

34
00:05:22,896 --> 00:05:23,854
What about the money?

35
00:05:24,437 --> 00:05:27,395
By tonight, ten million dollars
will be transferred...

36
00:05:27,396 --> 00:05:28,604
to your contact in Dubai.

37
00:05:35,979 --> 00:05:38,187
Now I want to speak
to the passengers, alone.

38
00:06:00,312 --> 00:06:01,187
Attention, everyone.

39
00:06:03,479 --> 00:06:06,437
You may now remove your blindfolds

40
00:06:06,687 --> 00:06:07,937
and open the window shades.

41
00:06:14,646 --> 00:06:15,646
Please don't worry.

42
00:06:16,604 --> 00:06:19,271
I'm Ajay Sanyal,
Chief of India's Intelligence Bureau.

43
00:06:20,396 --> 00:06:22,229
I'm pleased to inform you

44
00:06:22,854 --> 00:06:25,354
that our negotiations
have been successful.

45
00:06:28,021 --> 00:06:30,312
By tomorrow evening, all of you

46
00:06:30,896 --> 00:06:33,229
will be returning safely to India.

47
00:06:35,187 --> 00:06:39,146
Our nation will forever remain
grateful for your courage

48
00:06:39,771 --> 00:06:42,937
and resilience during this difficult time.

49
00:06:44,229 --> 00:06:45,896
Glory to...

50
00:06:56,687 --> 00:06:58,771
Glory to...

51
00:07:13,187 --> 00:07:14,312
Glory indeed.

52
00:07:27,729 --> 00:07:30,479
You Hindus are a bunch of cowards, yes?

53
00:07:32,396 --> 00:07:36,771
Mr. Intelligence,
we'd better get our money by tonight.

54
00:07:37,896 --> 00:07:40,437
Wasn't your land once
called the "Golden Bird"?

55
00:07:41,521 --> 00:07:42,687
Tonight, we strip it of its gold,

56
00:07:44,104 --> 00:07:46,521
tomorrow, the bird
will be gone for good.

57
00:07:58,854 --> 00:07:59,771
Mr. Sanyal...

58
00:08:03,937 --> 00:08:05,271
we live just across the border, you know.

59
00:08:06,896 --> 00:08:08,479
If you think you've the balls,

60
00:08:09,521 --> 00:08:11,396
go ahead. Do your worst.

61
00:08:21,854 --> 00:08:22,896
Sir, please don't take this personally,

62
00:08:24,021 --> 00:08:25,979
but apart from you, the rest of our

63
00:08:26,354 --> 00:08:28,062
negotiation team is completely
inexperienced.

64
00:08:28,729 --> 00:08:32,061
Even if our commandos
had stormed that plane,

65
00:08:32,062 --> 00:08:34,187
it would've been a better strategy
for India's reputation.

66
00:08:34,812 --> 00:08:37,271
So you're telling me

67
00:08:37,604 --> 00:08:39,186
it's a "better strategy"
to risk 160 lives just

68
00:08:39,187 --> 00:08:41,271
to protect our country's reputation?

69
00:08:41,479 --> 00:08:43,187
I've handled this kind
of situation before.

70
00:08:45,062 --> 00:08:46,062
And let's be frank, sir,

71
00:08:46,687 --> 00:08:49,354
our country's not prepared
to handle this kind of adversity.

72
00:08:50,062 --> 00:08:51,479
So then we'd better start preparing.

73
00:08:53,729 --> 00:08:54,771
We've exhausted every other option anyway.

74
00:08:55,687 --> 00:08:56,812
We begged the UN,

75
00:08:57,146 --> 00:08:58,436
we pleaded with the US,

76
00:08:58,437 --> 00:09:00,604
and they laughed at every
diplomatic solution we offered.

77
00:09:01,687 --> 00:09:04,187
Sir, I'm sorry, I'm being rather blunt,
but I have no choice.

78
00:09:04,646 --> 00:09:06,187
They barged into Kashmir, Kargil.

79
00:09:06,562 --> 00:09:07,936
Next, it'll be Hyderabad,

80
00:09:07,937 --> 00:09:11,687
and all we'll do is stand around
singing patriotic songs.

81
00:09:17,021 --> 00:09:20,062
Sir, to land a punch,
you must first make a fist.

82
00:09:21,229 --> 00:09:24,854
We must infiltrate the very core
of terrorism in Pakistan.

83
00:09:26,229 --> 00:09:28,771
So if they even dream of harming India...

84
00:09:29,562 --> 00:09:31,521
we should be waiting for them there,
like a nightmare.

85
00:09:32,229 --> 00:09:34,062
And sir, I have a unique plan
to make that happen.

86
00:09:34,396 --> 00:09:36,354
Come on, Sanyal,
what are you on about?

87
00:09:36,562 --> 00:09:39,229
The whole world saw your plan fail
spectacularly in Kandahar.

88
00:09:40,021 --> 00:09:41,479
You handle Indian Intelligence,

89
00:09:41,771 --> 00:09:43,104
let me handle the international side.

90
00:09:45,229 --> 00:09:47,271
Sir, did I share my Kashmir doctrine
with you?

91
00:09:47,729 --> 00:09:49,937
Now that's what I call
"Hope for Peace."

92
00:09:54,646 --> 00:09:55,895
What's the good news, ma'am?

93
00:09:55,896 --> 00:09:57,978
My husband just got a job
as a security guard at SBI.

94
00:09:57,979 --> 00:09:59,521
- Congratulations, ma'am.
- You too have some.

95
00:09:59,896 --> 00:10:00,936
Remember, I told you about it earlier?

96
00:10:00,937 --> 00:10:02,853
- Congratulations, madam.
- Come here. Thank you.

97
00:10:02,854 --> 00:10:04,311
- When did he get the job?
- Today.

98
00:10:04,312 --> 00:10:05,811
- I'm throwing a party tonight.
- Slow down.

99
00:10:05,812 --> 00:10:06,937
Sir, sir, sir! Stop!

100
00:10:07,687 --> 00:10:08,561
Sir, please stop.

101
00:10:08,562 --> 00:10:09,729
- Hold that for me, will you?
- Sure.

102
00:10:11,812 --> 00:10:13,645
- Stop! Stop!
- Stop the car!

103
00:10:13,646 --> 00:10:15,146
Stop!

104
00:10:20,062 --> 00:10:23,561
Yadav, that car's going way over
the speed limit... stop it!

105
00:10:23,562 --> 00:10:25,979
Shut all the doors of Parliament,
now! Hurry!

106
00:10:26,437 --> 00:10:28,521
- It's heading towards the VVIP gate!
- Stop it!

107
00:10:35,604 --> 00:10:37,521
The car's crashed near Gate No. 11!

108
00:10:37,646 --> 00:10:40,020
Close every entrance
to the Parliament, quick!

109
00:10:40,021 --> 00:10:41,021
Do it now!

110
00:10:43,729 --> 00:10:46,145
At approximately 11:40 a.m.,

111
00:10:46,146 --> 00:10:49,436
