high level bureaucrats

1546
01:50:56,687 --> 01:50:58,729
and officers were part
of this deal.

1547
01:50:59,146 --> 01:51:01,895
Millions were transferred from
Javed Khanani's London account

1548
01:51:01,896 --> 01:51:05,479
into the offshore accounts of
our minister and these officers.

1549
01:51:05,687 --> 01:51:08,354
Sir, I think we should take
immediate action against them.

1550
01:51:10,896 --> 01:51:12,562
We're powerless against them.

1551
01:51:13,354 --> 01:51:14,228
Sir...

1552
01:51:14,229 --> 01:51:15,729
Even if we expose them,

1553
01:51:16,354 --> 01:51:19,979
these ministers
will cry political vendetta

1554
01:51:20,604 --> 01:51:22,021
and get us blacklisted.

1555
01:51:22,146 --> 01:51:24,562
But, sir, we can't stay silent either.

1556
01:51:25,104 --> 01:51:25,979
Bansal,

1557
01:51:27,354 --> 01:51:30,187
do you know
the best thing about fate?

1558
01:51:33,771 --> 01:51:35,354
It shifts when the time is right.

1559
01:51:37,812 --> 01:51:39,021
Our time will come.

1560
01:51:42,604 --> 01:51:43,604
Until then,

1561
01:51:44,021 --> 01:51:44,937
watch...

1562
01:51:46,354 --> 01:51:47,229
and wait...

1563
01:51:55,396 --> 01:51:57,771
Khanani sahab,
we're heading out in five minutes.

1564
01:51:58,271 --> 01:51:59,937
Don't worry, we'll be there.

1565
01:52:01,312 --> 01:52:02,187
Goodbye.

1566
01:52:02,937 --> 01:52:04,020
- Donga!
- Yeah?

1567
01:52:04,021 --> 01:52:04,978
Go inside

1568
01:52:04,979 --> 01:52:06,228
- and tell Rehman bhai to move it.
- Okay.

1569
01:52:06,229 --> 01:52:08,228
Khanani keeps blowing up
my phone from the factory.

1570
01:52:08,229 --> 01:52:09,936
- Donga! Donga!
- It's clear everyone's waiting on us.

1571
01:52:09,937 --> 01:52:11,562
- Yes, bhai?
- Get the engines running.

1572
01:52:12,021 --> 01:52:13,270
- Yes, bhai.
- Bhai, he...

1573
01:52:13,271 --> 01:52:15,103
Take the goods
and leave for Khanani's.

1574
01:52:15,104 --> 01:52:16,645
- Faizal has suddenly fallen sick.
- Let's go.

1575
01:52:16,646 --> 01:52:17,603
- Start the car.
- I'm taking him to the hospital.

1576
01:52:17,604 --> 01:52:18,686
We'll come with you, bhai.

1577
01:52:18,687 --> 01:52:20,311
You all go.
I've got Donga with me.

1578
01:52:20,312 --> 01:52:22,354
Listen, make sure they pay
the full amount upfront.

1579
01:52:22,479 --> 01:52:23,812
Khananis can't be trusted.

1580
01:52:24,312 --> 01:52:25,186
Okay.

1581
01:52:25,187 --> 01:52:26,145
Let's go.

1582
01:52:26,146 --> 01:52:27,312
Drive already!
Go.

1583
01:52:27,812 --> 01:52:29,687
All of you go with Rehman bhai.

1584
01:52:29,896 --> 01:52:30,812
Let's go.

1585
01:52:31,812 --> 01:52:33,186
What are you lot waiting for?

1586
01:52:33,187 --> 01:52:35,312
- Get in. Get moving.
- Get in the car.

1587
01:52:35,812 --> 01:52:37,396
- Is everything loaded or not?
- Yes, bhai.

1588
01:52:58,312 --> 01:52:59,271
What's on your mind?

1589
01:53:00,354 --> 01:53:01,271
Everything alright?

1590
01:53:46,104 --> 01:53:47,187
Salam alaykum.

1591
01:53:48,229 --> 01:53:49,479
As promised, delivery on Thursday.

1592
01:53:52,187 --> 01:53:53,896
Wa'alaykumu s-salam.

1593
01:53:54,146 --> 01:53:55,937
- Everything alright, Cheema sahab?
- All good.

1594
01:53:57,604 --> 01:53:59,021
- How are you, bhai?
- Uzair miyan!

1595
01:54:03,604 --> 01:54:04,479
Check everything.

1596
01:54:05,729 --> 01:54:07,396
We've got everything in the list.

1597
01:54:08,771 --> 01:54:09,646
Amazing.

1598
01:54:10,937 --> 01:54:13,937
Ajmal, Ismail,
don't be shy, go on, pick it up.

1599
01:54:15,021 --> 01:54:16,187
We brought them especially for you.

1600
01:54:46,146 --> 01:54:47,646
Rehman really outdid himself.

1601
01:54:48,604 --> 01:54:49,479
Why didn't he show up?

1602
01:54:50,146 --> 01:54:51,979
He got tied up somewhere,
so he couldn't come.

1603
01:54:52,521 --> 01:54:53,396
He has sent his regards.

1604
01:55:06,979 --> 01:55:09,271
Watch out, Donga!

1605
01:55:52,687 --> 01:55:53,729
Rehman!

1606
01:55:56,646 --> 01:55:59,271
Uzair, Hamza,
you're sure you don't want some?

1607
01:55:59,604 --> 01:56:01,104
No, Javed bhai.
We'll head out as soon

1608
01:56:01,521 --> 01:56:03,437
- as the boys finish loading up.
- Don't put it in the boot,

1609
01:56:03,604 --> 01:56:04,478
keep it in the back seat.

1610
01:56:04,479 --> 01:56:05,437
It won't take long.

1611
01:56:07,437 --> 01:56:09,770
- The cry of Takbir...
- Allah is the greatest!

1612
01:56:09,771 --> 01:56:12,229
So, are the boys ready
to leave tomorrow?

1613
01:56:13,771 --> 01:56:14,646
No.

1614
01:56:18,062 --> 01:56:19,353
- Donga, Siyahi...
- Yes, bhai?

1615
01:56:19,354 --> 01:56:20,687
- You two get going,
- What about you, bhai?

1616
01:56:20,937 --> 01:56:23,271
and tell Uzair to inform Jameel.

1617
01:56:24,271 --> 01:56:25,854
But Khan bhai, he's the SP!

1618
01:56:30,187 --> 01:56:31,604
If you two stay here,

1619
01:56:31,979 --> 01:56:33,187
this boy won't make it out alive.

1620
01:56:48,979 --> 01:56:50,562
Weren't they supposed
to move on Friday?

1621
01:56:51,312 --> 01:56:52,979
Yes, that was the plan.

1622
01:56:54,729 --> 01:56:56,271
But we learned someone tipped off

1623
01:56:58,562 --> 01:57:02,604
Indian Intelligence about our arrival.

1624
01:57:05,271 --> 01:57:06,729
They were waiting for us.

1625
01:57:07,646 --> 01:57:10,729
Rehman, my friend...

1626
01:57:11,479 --> 01:57:13,436
Should I punch just your ticket
to heaven,

1627
01:57:13,437 --> 01:57:16,021
or do you want to take your wife
and kid along too?

1628
01:57:16,812 --> 01:57:18,312
Once they arrest me,

1629
01:57:18,771 --> 01:57:20,311
take him straight to the hospital, understand?

1630
01:57:20,312 --> 01:57:21,271
Rehman...

1631
01:57:21,812 --> 01:57:23,271
They won't hurt you.

1632
01:57:51,687 --> 01:57:52,562
Anyway...

1633
01:57:55,896 --> 01:57:57,687
This plan is on hold until Bade sahab

1634
01:57:59,562 --> 01:58:00,771
gives the green light.

1635
01:58:21,562 --> 01:58:23,229
And the best part is...

1636
01:58:25,604 --> 01:58:27,187
we know exactly who the snitch is.

1637
01:58:54,062 --> 01:58:54,937
Come.

1638
01:58:59,437 --> 01:59:00,437
Uzair miyan, please join us.

1639
01:59:04,854 --> 01:59:05,729
Follow me.

1640
01:59:14,979 --> 01:59:15,896
Speak up!

1641
01:59:16,479 --> 01:59:17,437
Speak up now!

1642
01:59:21,312 --> 01:59:22,604
Come on, Sajid,

1643
01:59:22,771 --> 01:59:24,729
what are you doing,
having sex with him or what?

1644
01:59:25,562 --> 01:59:27,437
He's an Indian spy.

1645
01:59:28,104 --> 01:59:29,854
These guys are tough as nails.

1646
01:59:31,562 --> 01:59:32,811
You whip him like that,

1647
01:59:32,812 --> 01:59:35,687
he'll flip it on you
and make you his ride.

1648
01:59:36,771 --> 01:59:37,812
Wait, let me show you
how this is done.

1649
01:59:40,687 --> 01:59:42,812
After the 1971 war,

1650
01:59:43,729 --> 01:59:47,021
there was an atmosphere
of gloom in Pakistan.

1651
01:59:47,854 --> 01:59:49,062
I was six years old...

1652
01:59:50,437 --> 01:59:51,396
listening to the radio...

1653
01:59:52,729 --> 01:59:53,729
At that time,

1654
01:59:54,437 --> 01:59:57,979
Zia-ul-Haq said something
that I never forgot.

1655
01:59:58,812 --> 02:00:01,146
Bleed India with a thousand cuts.

1656
02:00:02,687 --> 02:00:04,521
Just like these

1657
02:00:05,146 --> 02:00:08,229
countless tiny incisions in his body,

1658
02:00:09,604 --> 02:00:10,646
I swear on God,

1659
02:00:11,812 --> 02:00:14,812
I will make that country suffer
a fate worse than this.

1660
02:00:17,812 --> 02:00:20,021
But for now, in the name of Allah,

1661
02:00:20,396 --> 02:00:21,396
let's begin with this.

1662
02:00:22,854 --> 02:00:23,771
Speak up.

1663
02:00:25,187 --> 02:00:28,853
How many infidel agents
came with you?

1664
02:00:28,854 --> 02:00:30,312
Where are they deployed?

1665
02:00:33,104 --> 02:00:33,978
Karachi?

1666
02:00:33,979 --> 02:00:35,271
Rawalpindi?

1667
02:00:35,937 --> 02:00:37,521
Get talking, son.

1668
02:00:44,604 --> 02:00:47,229
I don't want to kill you.

1669
02:00:47,437 --> 02:00:50,271
Just tell me where they are.

1670
02:00:50,896 --> 02:00:51,854
How many of them are here?

1671
02:00:52,146 --> 02:00:53,854
You crossed into my country!

1672
02:00:54,812 --> 02:00:55,687
Talk!

1673
02:00:56,229 --> 02:00:57,271
Speak up!

1674
02:01:03,521 --> 02:01:05,853
These bastards don't understand
the language of love.

1675
02:01:05,854 --> 02:01:08,437
Tell me!
Where are they deployed?

1676
02:01:09,521 --> 02:01:10,437
Speak up!

1677
02:01:14,437 --> 02:01:15,312
Speak up!

1678
02:01:31,021 --> 02:01:32,936
Yeah, Donga,
everything alright at the hospital?

1679
02:01:32,937 --> 02:01:35,687
Bhai, they've arrested Rehman bhai
at the Mai Kolach bridge!

1680
02:01:40,437 --> 02:01:41,604
Who dared to do that?!

1681
02:01:41,979 --> 02:01:44,396
That rascal SP...
Chaudhary Aslam!

1682
02:01:46,729 --> 02:01:48,104
The SP?! Dang!

1683
02:01:48,479 --> 02:01:51,229
Rehman bhai said you must
inform Jameel bhai immediately.

1684
02:01:59,354 --> 02:02:01,728
Change of pace and a great breakthrough.

1685
02:02:01,729 --> 02:02:05,186
Hey Uzair, my boy,
what made you think of me today?

1686
02:02:05,187 --> 02:02:06,729
Jameel bhai, listen carefully,

1687
02:02:06,979 --> 02:02:10,145
SP Aslam has arrested Rehman
at Mai Kolach bridge.

1688
02:02:10,146 --> 02:02:11,896
What? Rehman got arrested?

1689
02:02:12,187 --> 02:02:13,478
Don't worry, my boy,

1690
02:02:13,479 --> 02:02:14,937
your Uncle Jameel
will sort everything out.

1691
02:02:15,104 --> 02:02:15,978
I'll take care of it.

1692
02:02:15,979 --> 02:02:17,771
Just hurry, please.
Do something fast.

1693
02:02:19,146 --> 02:02:20,854
The ball was close.
A beautiful shot.

1694
02:02:22,937 --> 02:02:26,562
Come on, Misba!
Another dropped catch?

1695
02:02:26,937 --> 02:02:28,187
I had money riding on that!

1696
02:02:31,229 --> 02:02:32,937
Jameel bhai will handle it.

1697
02:02:33,312 --> 02:02:35,646
- We need to gather all the boys--
- Head back home.

1698
02:02:38,687 --> 02:02:40,271
Uzair, home, now!

1699
02:02:55,354 --> 02:02:57,104
I've waited 12 years...

1700
02:02:58,312 --> 02:03:01,312
to see your blood on my shirt.

1701
02:03:02,187 --> 02:03:04,354
This is Rehman Dakait's blood
we're talking about, SP sahab,

1702
02:03:06,062 --> 02:03:07,312
spill it wisely.

1703
02:03:12,937 --> 02:03:13,854
Thrash the bastard!

1704
02:03:27,146 --> 02:03:28,062
Aqlaakh!

1705
02:03:28,187 --> 02:03:30,521
Get everyone in Lyari moving.

1706
02:03:30,729 --> 02:03:32,145
I want updates on every step

1707
02:03:32,146 --> 02:03:34,479
- that LTF van takes.
- Okay, bhai.

1708
02:03:34,979 --> 02:03:35,896
Aqlaakh!

1709
02:03:38,687 --> 02:03:39,562
Aqlaakh!

1710
02:03:40,687 --> 02:03:41,562
Yes, brother?

1711
02:03:43,271 --> 02:03:44,229
You...

1712
02:03:44,646 --> 02:03:45,646
Have you lost your mind?

1713
02:03:48,229 --> 02:03:49,353
What did you put in the kid's food?

1714
02:03:49,354 --> 02:03:50,729
How can you accuse me like that?

1715
02:03:51,271 --> 02:03:53,021
- I've worked here 40 years!
- Get talking, Aqlaakh!

1716
02:03:53,229 --> 02:03:54,312
I don't know what you're talking about.

1717
02:03:56,062 --> 02:03:58,896
Speak before I finish you.

1718
02:04:00,854 --> 02:04:02,061
Who's with sister-in-law
at the hospital?

1719
02:04:02,062 --> 02:04:03,020
Don't know, bhai.

1720
02:04:03,021 --> 02:04:04,229
Send someone there right now!

1721
02:04:09,104 --> 02:04:10,396
Where are they taking
Rehman bhai?

1722
02:04:10,979 --> 02:04:12,811
- I swear, I don't know.
- Don't know?

1723
02:04:12,812 --> 02:04:13,812
What are you talking about?

1724
02:04:14,687 --> 02:04:18,479
- Come here.
- Where are you taking me, brother?

1725
02:04:23,854 --> 02:04:26,811
- For God's sake, let me go.
- I'm giving you one last chance, Aqlaakh.

1726
02:04:26,812 --> 02:04:27,978
Speak up, or I'll carve out your kidneys

1727
02:04:27,979 --> 02:04:30,271
- and liver and make you eat them yourself.
- I don't know... I really don't know.

1728
02:04:30,396 --> 02:04:31,270
You sure?

1729
02:04:31,271 --> 02:04:32,978
I don't know, brother.

1730
02:04:32,979 --> 02:04:34,562
Hamza, what are you doing?

1731
02:04:34,687 --> 02:04:35,562
Stop right there!

1732
02:04:35,937 --> 02:04:37,271
What are you doing, brother?

1733
02:04:38,812 --> 02:04:40,854
- Who's behind this?
- Hamza, what's gotten into you?

1734
02:04:40,979 --> 02:04:42,479
- I don't know, brother.
- You really don't know?

1735
02:04:42,604 --> 02:04:43,562
I don't know.

1736
02:04:44,271 --> 02:04:46,145
- Hamza...
- Arshad Pappu!

1737
02:04:46,146 --> 02:04:47,104
Who?!

1738
02:04:48,229 --> 02:04:50,187
- Arshad Pappu!
- What?

1739
02:04:51,896 --> 02:04:54,062
Arshad Pappu!

1740
02:04:54,812 --> 02:04:56,812
Arshad Pappu?

1741
02:05:03,271 --> 02:05:06,812
They gave me a liquid
to mix into Faizal's milk...

1742
02:05:12,521 --> 02:05:14,437
How much did you sell your soul for,
Aqlaakh?

1743
02:05:15,271 --> 02:05:16,146
Speak up!

1744
02:05:16,562 --> 02:05:18,937
How dare you...
you betrayed my brother!

1745
02:05:19,104 --> 02:05:20,854
You betrayed Rehman bhai!

1746
02:05:21,229 --> 02:05:22,896
Brother, it was a mistake...

1747
02:05:23,187 --> 02:05:26,145
Brother... it was a mistake...

1748
02:05:26,146 --> 02:05:29,229
Brother, no...
it was a mistake...

1749
02:05:29,479 --> 02:05:31,061
Brother, please forgive me.

1750
02:05:31,062 --> 02:05:32,020
Yalina.

1751
02:05:32,021 --> 02:05:33,520
I've been calling you forever...
Where are you?

1752
02:05:33,521 --> 02:05:35,645
Yalina, I'm busy with something.

1753
02:05:35,646 --> 02:05:36,729
I'll call you back.

1754
02:05:37,104 --> 02:05:40,062
My love, at least check
your messages.

1755
02:05:40,521 --> 02:05:42,021
I sent you a gift.

1756
02:05:42,812 --> 02:05:43,686
Keep an eye on your dad.

1757
02:05:43,687 --> 02:05:46,146
Keep an eye on the SP.
Dad-SP-SP-Dad.

1758
02:05:46,771 --> 02:05:48,895
I've kept such a good eye on them,

1759
02:05:48,896 --> 02:05:51,354
you'll surely run here
and kiss me when you find out.

1760
02:05:53,271 --> 02:05:55,854
Fine, Lyari is yours
for the taking.

1761
02:05:56,562 --> 02:05:59,062
SP, you'll take care of the rest, right?

1762
02:05:59,979 --> 02:06:01,271
Yalina, where exactly
are you right now?

1763
02:06:01,396 --> 02:06:02,312
Are you actually coming here?

1764
02:06:02,479 --> 02:06:03,354
Dolmen Mall.

1765
02:06:03,646 --> 02:06:05,020
I'm dead serious, Yalina.

1766
02:06:05,021 --> 02:06:07,186
Leave the mall, go to my place,
and switch off your phone.

1767
02:06:07,187 --> 02:06:08,937
And don't step out till I get there.

1768
02:06:13,396 --> 02:06:14,271
Hamza?

1769
02:06:14,479 --> 02:06:15,937
- Yalina, go home.
- Hello?

1770
02:06:32,479 --> 02:06:34,271
One run from two balls.

1771
02:06:35,062 --> 02:06:37,521
The moment the shot was taken, they ran.
A thunderous appeal goes up,

1772
02:06:38,396 --> 02:06:40,562
but the umpire isn't convinced at all.

1773
02:06:41,104 --> 02:06:43,479
Both sides are now level on 195.

1774
02:06:45,229 --> 02:06:46,103
Concerned...

1775
02:06:46,104 --> 02:06:48,021
First, I want Rehman's head...

1776
02:06:48,687 --> 02:06:49,604
and then Lyari...

1777
02:06:50,021 --> 02:06:51,478
But still hanging on to plenty of hope.

1778
02:06:51,479 --> 02:06:53,187
One run needed off one ball.

1779
02:07:12,729 --> 02:07:14,562
First, I want Rehman's head...

1780
02:07:15,896 --> 02:07:16,896
and then Lyari...

1781
02:07:17,979 --> 02:07:19,354
at any cost.

1782
02:07:20,687 --> 02:07:24,521
And it'll be my job to get Rehman
out of the house alone.

1783
02:07:26,812 --> 02:07:29,187
Fine, Lyari is yours
for the taking.

1784
02:07:29,312 --> 02:07:30,271
Enjoy.

1785
02:07:30,812 --> 02:07:33,561
But listen, don't go sniffing around

1786
02:07:33,562 --> 02:07:36,021
those Muslim Movement Party beggars.

1787
02:07:36,271 --> 02:07:38,062
They're bloody broke.

1788
02:07:38,687 --> 02:07:41,479
Don't worry, Arshad,
you're my boy.

1789
02:07:42,479 --> 02:07:45,229
Take a puff...

1790
02:07:46,062 --> 02:07:50,937
- SP, you'll take care of the rest, right?
- And let the sorrows fade

1791
02:07:53,562 --> 02:07:56,770
Chant day and night...

1792
02:07:56,771 --> 02:08:04,646
Glory to Lord Krishna and Lord Ram

1793
02:08:08,646 --> 02:08:10,646
Jameel sahab, Hamza Ali Mazari here.

1794
02:08:11,354 --> 02:08:14,521
You've got one hour to have
Rehman bhai at Shershah Bridge, alive.

1795
02:08:16,062 --> 02:08:17,895
If he's not there,
this video becomes tonight's

1796
02:08:17,896 --> 02:08:19,229
breaking news on every channel.

1797
02:08:20,854 --> 02:08:23,479
Choose your next step wisely,
Jameel sahab...

1798
02:08:27,229 --> 02:08:30,271
You see, your daughter is with me.

1799
02:08:33,479 --> 02:08:34,354
Yalina!

1800
02:08:35,771 --> 02:08:36,812
Yalina!

1801
02:08:37,521 --> 02:08:38,687
Yalina, where are you?!

1802
02:08:39,104 --> 02:08:40,062
Yalina!

1803
02:08:40,229 --> 02:08:41,145
What's going on?

1804
02:08:41,146 --> 02:08:42,187
Why are you shouting like this?

1805
02:08:42,354 --> 02:08:43,271
Where's Yalina?

1806
02:08:43,562 --> 02:08:44,604
She's at a mall.

1807
02:08:44,729 --> 02:08:45,979
She's not at any stupid mall!

1808
02:08:51,229 --> 02:08:53,146
Think you can handle
the pain, kiddo?

1809
02:08:53,854 --> 02:08:56,812
I'll try... kiddo.

1810
02:09:01,229 --> 02:09:02,729
SWINE JAMALI

1811
02:09:07,187 --> 02:09:10,229
I was about to crack his
head open when you called.

1812
02:09:10,521 --> 02:09:13,146
Aslam, don't kill Rehman.

1813
02:09:13,604 --> 02:09:14,479
What?

1814
02:09:14,604 --> 02:09:16,271
Check your phone.

1815
02:09:20,146 --> 02:09:21,937
First, I want Rehman's head...

1816
02:09:22,687 --> 02:09:23,687
and then Lyari...

1817
02:09:24,979 --> 02:09:26,437
at any cost.

1818
02:09:29,437 --> 02:09:30,521
Where did you get this from?

1819
02:09:30,646 --> 02:09:31,771
It doesn't matter!

1820
02:09:32,062 --> 02:09:33,396
If that video comes out,

1821
02:09:33,604 --> 02:09:36,646
my career is over
and my daughter's as good as dead.

1822
02:09:38,604 --> 02:09:39,979
I can't hear you.

1823
02:09:55,937 --> 02:09:56,937
Any word on their van?

1824
02:09:58,562 --> 02:10:01,520
How is it so hard
to track one vehicle?

1825
02:10:01,521 --> 02:10:02,479
Hamza...

1826
02:10:02,687 --> 02:10:03,896
Hamza, the SP isn't listening.

1827
02:10:04,396 --> 02:10:05,812
He's not answering my calls either.

1828
02:10:05,937 --> 02:10:07,978
I want to know where SP is, at any cost!

1829
02:10:07,979 --> 02:10:09,479
Where's the Lyari Task Force office?

1830
02:10:14,771 --> 02:10:16,062
I won't repeat myself.

1831
02:10:28,896 --> 02:10:30,437
What are you doing here, ma'am?

1832
02:10:30,646 --> 02:10:31,729
The school's closed.

1833
02:10:31,937 --> 02:10:33,521
You can't be in here
without permission.

1834
02:10:33,812 --> 02:10:34,854
Please leave.

1835
02:10:54,062 --> 02:10:56,479
How dare you arrest my brother,
you rascal!

1836
02:10:57,687 --> 02:10:58,896
- Sir, you need to see this.
- Thrash them.

1837
02:11:02,062 --> 02:11:03,271
How dare you?!

1838
02:11:03,937 --> 02:11:08,521
You've got a lot of nerve these days,
don't you?

1839
02:11:09,396 --> 02:11:10,271
Rascal...

1840
02:11:13,187 --> 02:11:14,104
You...

1841
02:11:15,229 --> 02:11:17,603
You shouldn't have done this.

1842
02:11:17,604 --> 02:11:20,353
You shouldn't have taken my brother.

1843
02:11:20,354 --> 02:11:21,854
You'll pay for what you've done!

1844
02:11:22,021 --> 02:11:26,604
Till that Aslam doesn't
release my brother,

1845
02:11:26,854 --> 02:11:30,686
these rascals will stay
hanging right here.

1846
02:11:30,687 --> 02:11:33,396
Tell me where is Rehman bhai!

1847
02:11:33,562 --> 02:11:34,771
Tell me now!

1848
02:11:39,146 --> 02:11:40,354
Don't spare anyone!

1849
02:11:40,729 --> 02:11:42,729
Let them all stay hanging here!

1850
02:11:46,896 --> 02:11:50,312
How dare that SP Aslam arrest my brother!

1851
02:11:50,854 --> 02:11:53,146
Turn them black and blue.

1852
02:11:53,312 --> 02:11:55,687
He should know the consequences!

1853
02:11:56,062 --> 02:11:56,937
You...

1854
02:12:15,687 --> 02:12:16,854
SP Chaudhary Aslam,

1855
02:12:18,937 --> 02:12:20,770
the blaze that'll rise
out of Lyari Task Force

1856
02:12:20,771 --> 02:12:22,937
will reduce Karachi to ashes.

1857
02:12:25,354 --> 02:12:28,771
Your 40 men won't even
have bodies left to bury.

1858
02:12:32,187 --> 02:12:33,437
In the next 30 minutes,

1859
02:12:34,521 --> 02:12:36,437
I want Rehman bhai
at Shershah Bridge,

1860
02:12:37,479 --> 02:12:38,687
alive and unharmed.

1861
02:12:41,104 --> 02:12:41,979
Goodbye.

1862
02:13:48,479 --> 02:13:49,521
Be careful, bhai.

1863
02:13:51,604 --> 02:13:53,229
Which one of you is Hamza?

1864
02:14:00,937 --> 02:14:01,854
Come here.

1865
02:14:06,271 --> 02:14:07,146
Hamza...

1866
02:14:27,062 --> 02:14:31,187
You lit a spark and thought
you could control the fire?

1867
02:14:34,729 --> 02:14:36,479
Don't fool yourself.

1868
02:14:38,104 --> 02:14:39,811
There's a whole heap of gunpowder here

1869
02:14:39,812 --> 02:14:41,812
enough to reduce men like you to ash.

1870
02:15:25,187 --> 02:15:27,271
You are great, Rehman Baloch!

1871
02:15:34,062 --> 02:15:42,896
Rehman! Rehman! Rehman!

1872
02:15:43,021 --> 02:15:48,187
Rehman! Rehman! Rehman!

1873
02:15:52,354 --> 02:15:54,812
Rehman Baloch! Rehman Baloch!

1874
02:16:16,937 --> 02:16:18,104
Come here.

1875
02:16:26,479 --> 02:16:28,229
Who told you about
the Lyari Task Force office?

1876
02:16:29,104 --> 02:16:30,271
Jameel sahab.

1877
02:16:31,104 --> 02:16:32,479
He was worried about you.

1878
02:16:35,604 --> 02:16:37,854
In politics,
all anyone worries about is the throne.

1879
02:16:40,062 --> 02:16:40,979
Bhai,

1880
02:16:41,729 --> 02:16:43,437
he's got a thing going
on with Jameel Jamali's daughter.

1881
02:16:45,229 --> 02:16:49,354
The other day, our boys kept saying,
"Yalina Jamali!"

1882
02:16:50,104 --> 02:16:51,812
Must say that's a big jump!

1883
02:16:53,937 --> 02:16:55,104
Is it love or just lust?

1884
02:16:57,521 --> 02:16:58,396
Love.

1885
02:16:58,854 --> 02:16:59,896
He's brought her home.

1886
02:17:00,604 --> 02:17:02,812
She's staying with him now.

1887
02:17:03,687 --> 02:17:06,521
Poor Jameel's already
lost his daughter.

1888
02:17:07,271 --> 02:17:09,062
And God willing,
he's also about to lose his throne.

1889
02:17:13,312 --> 02:17:15,687
We'll have to find a way to deal
with SP and Arshad Pappu.

1890
02:17:47,562 --> 02:17:48,812
Don't you want to go home?

1891
02:17:49,396 --> 02:17:52,229
If you want to go to my place,
then go.

1892
02:17:54,062 --> 02:17:55,396
I didn't come here just to run back.

1893
02:18:16,062 --> 02:18:17,229
Have we received Khanani's money?

1894
02:18:18,104 --> 02:18:19,062
We've got six crores so far, bhai.

1895
02:18:19,229 --> 02:18:20,936
Once the remaining
six crores come in,

1896
02:18:20,937 --> 02:18:22,686
no one will be able
to beat our party in Lyari.

1897
02:18:22,687 --> 02:18:24,520
Rehman bhai!

1898
02:18:24,521 --> 02:18:27,021
Your throne in politics
is now guaranteed.

1899
02:18:27,271 --> 02:18:28,145
Uzair.

1900
02:18:28,146 --> 02:18:29,146
Hamza.

1901
02:18:29,896 --> 02:18:30,936
Come on, hurry up,

1902
02:18:30,937 --> 02:18:33,771
you're missing the most incredible
moment of our lives.

1903
02:18:34,562 --> 02:18:36,521
We've been eagerly waiting
for you to join us.

1904
02:18:39,312 --> 02:18:40,270
Come.

1905
02:18:40,271 --> 02:18:42,229
- How many have they lost so far?
- God willing, my brother.

1906
02:18:42,479 --> 02:18:43,978
Paradise awaits you.

1907
02:18:43,979 --> 02:18:45,061
If you bring down the ambient
sound just a little bit...

1908
02:18:45,062 --> 02:18:46,561
- Start a fire on several floors.
- Salam.

1909
02:18:46,562 --> 02:18:47,978
- What you are seeing there right now...
- Look, Rehman bhai,

1910
02:18:47,979 --> 02:18:49,811
this is the destruction your guns
and ammo have unleashed.

1911
02:18:49,812 --> 02:18:51,978
Seems like Ghazwa-e-Hind
is starting right here from Mumbai.

1912
02:18:51,979 --> 02:18:55,436
- Please, come and have a seat.
- Come.

1913
02:18:55,437 --> 02:18:57,395
Rehman bhai!

1914
02:18:57,396 --> 02:19:00,187
But do not be mistaken...
It's been driven

1915
02:19:00,354 --> 02:19:03,686
by the terrorist who
attacked the CST Station.

1916
02:19:03,687 --> 02:19:07,104
This police van is not...
It is being driven

1917
02:19:07,354 --> 02:19:11,229
by the terrorist who
attacked the CST Station.

1918
02:19:11,354 --> 02:19:14,020
Presumably, these could
be the same two terrorists

1919
02:19:14,021 --> 02:19:15,896
whose pictures we
just showed you...

1920
02:19:18,021 --> 02:19:21,854
Which shocked many,
he was carrying an AK47 in his hand.

1921
02:19:22,062 --> 02:19:24,396
The look on his face
really told the story there.

1922
02:19:24,604 --> 02:19:28,312
A young man in a T-shirt
with a sling on his left arm...

1923
02:19:33,146 --> 02:19:36,062
And carrying what appears
to be either an AK47

1924
02:19:36,187 --> 02:19:38,104
or an... or a light machine gun.

1925
02:19:46,021 --> 02:19:47,061
As-salam alaykum, Ali.

1926
02:19:47,062 --> 02:19:48,062
You okay?

1927
02:19:48,354 --> 02:19:50,437
Your target, the Taj Hotel...

1928
02:19:50,937 --> 02:19:53,353
Media is giving it maximum coverage.

1929
02:19:53,354 --> 02:19:55,936
Trapped, still looking out
of their windows, waiting...

1930
02:19:55,937 --> 02:19:57,021
Did you start a fire yet?

1931
02:19:58,312 --> 02:19:59,687
My brother,

1932
02:20:00,812 --> 02:20:03,229
unless we see fire blazing,

1933
02:20:03,812 --> 02:20:05,354
the mood doesn't kick in.

1934
02:20:12,687 --> 02:20:14,354
We need to scare them
out of their minds.

1935
02:20:15,396 --> 02:20:18,604
In fact, there has been another
explosion right now.

1936
02:20:18,729 --> 02:20:21,604
Six blasts in about 35 minutes.

1937
02:20:22,521 --> 02:20:24,187
Rehman bhai, you've outdone yourself.

1938
02:20:41,229 --> 02:20:42,104
Remember...

1939
02:20:42,521 --> 02:20:46,687
Don't spare any Jews
or any foreigners in those rooms.

1940
02:20:47,812 --> 02:20:49,187
They are all infidels.

1941
02:20:49,646 --> 02:20:52,021
Women, kids, old people...

1942
02:20:52,979 --> 02:20:54,811
Kill them all, my brother.

1943
02:20:54,812 --> 02:20:56,437
Every single one
of them is an infidel.

1944
02:20:57,104 --> 02:20:58,396
Don't hesitate.

1945
02:21:07,396 --> 02:21:09,520
Operation Nariman House
commandos came

1946
02:21:09,521 --> 02:21:12,187
from the sky, not the street.

1947
02:21:17,146 --> 02:21:21,812
Listen, Indian commandos
are entering from the fifth floor.

1948
02:21:22,979 --> 02:21:24,729
Throw a handful of grenades at them.

1949
02:21:30,604 --> 02:21:32,603
More than 80 people are dead.

1950
02:21:32,604 --> 02:21:34,187
Several hundred were injured.

1951
02:21:34,437 --> 02:21:36,687
Forty hostages taken.

1952
02:21:37,646 --> 02:21:48,562
- The cry of Takbir...
- Allah is the greatest!

1953
02:21:48,771 --> 02:21:59,312
- The cry of Takbir...
- Allah is the greatest!

1954
02:22:00,479 --> 02:22:01,479
Allah is the greatest!

1955
02:22:16,562 --> 02:22:17,562
All right, God willing.

1956
02:22:19,229 --> 02:22:20,771
You have to be strong, my brother.

1957
02:22:21,104 --> 02:22:22,061
There's no need to panic.

1958
02:22:22,062 --> 02:22:23,020
- Not at all.
- God willing,

1959
02:22:23,021 --> 02:22:24,895
even if a bullet tears through you,

1960
02:22:24,896 --> 02:22:25,936
this mission still counts as a win.

1961
02:22:25,937 --> 02:22:29,146
- Yes, yes.
- Allah is waiting for you in heaven.

1962
02:22:29,271 --> 02:22:30,187
God willing.

1963
02:22:30,479 --> 02:22:32,312
Umar, take cover! Take cover now!

1964
02:22:36,562 --> 02:22:38,395
Put a bullet in every person
that you see.

1965
02:22:38,396 --> 02:22:40,229
We've already killed a commando
right at the damn entry.

1966
02:22:40,396 --> 02:22:41,520
Not yet, but soon, God willing.

1967
02:22:41,521 --> 02:22:44,896
All praise to Allah, all praise to
Allah...

1968
02:22:45,021 --> 02:22:46,312
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

1969
02:22:46,646 --> 02:22:49,229
Should we keep some alive
or just kill them all?

1970
02:22:49,729 --> 02:22:52,895
Listen up,
destroy each and every one of them.

1971
02:22:52,896 --> 02:22:54,021
And save your own ass from this mess.

1972
02:22:54,396 --> 02:22:56,812
The whole point is that
you hold them in such a way that

1973
02:22:57,229 --> 02:23:02,062
the bullet doesn't bounce off
and come flying back into your face.

1974
02:23:02,521 --> 02:23:03,603
God willing.

1975
02:23:03,604 --> 02:23:07,604
Make them sit facing forward,

1976
02:23:08,354 --> 02:23:10,979
and put a bullet straight through
the back of their head.

1977
02:23:11,271 --> 02:23:12,145
Hello?

1978
02:23:12,146 --> 02:23:15,103
- You talk to them, you talk to them.
- I have already talked to them.

1979
02:23:15,104 --> 02:23:19,228
I was talking to the Consulate
just a few seconds ago and...

1980
02:23:19,229 --> 02:23:20,229
Don't worry, ma'am.

1981
02:23:20,646 --> 02:23:25,021
Just sit back and relax, and don't worry,
and just wait for them to contact, okay?

1982
02:23:25,271 --> 02:23:26,396
Yes, sir.

1983
02:23:26,604 --> 02:23:28,186
If they contact right now,

1984
02:23:28,187 --> 02:23:31,937
maybe you're gonna, you know,
celebrate your Sabbath with your family.

1985
02:23:34,854 --> 02:23:35,979
- Hello.
- Okay.

1986
02:23:37,187 --> 02:23:38,312
You killed one?

1987
02:23:38,646 --> 02:23:40,354
No, both...

1988
02:23:41,229 --> 02:23:42,645
Give them an ultimatum!

1989
02:23:42,646 --> 02:23:44,479
This is just the trailer.

1990
02:23:44,771 --> 02:23:46,645
The whole movie is yet to come.

1991
02:23:46,646 --> 02:23:49,312
They should know this
is just the trailer.

1992
02:23:49,437 --> 02:23:51,229
The whole movie is yet to come.

1993
02:23:55,687 --> 02:23:57,854
We passed on the intel.

1994
02:23:59,187 --> 02:24:01,479
Got it there before time.

1995
02:24:02,562 --> 02:24:04,187
Then how the hell did this happen?

1996
02:24:06,937 --> 02:24:09,062
- We told them about 3rd October.
- Oh, come on!

1997
02:24:11,354 --> 02:24:12,646
We never told them about 26th November.

1998
02:24:14,937 --> 02:24:20,437
On that day, the intelligence department
received 309 different threat alerts.

1999
02:24:21,437 --> 02:24:24,062
Cochin, Manipur, Samba,
Delhi, Jaipur, Somnath!

2000
02:24:24,604 --> 02:24:26,354
Some real, most wrong.

2001
02:24:29,437 --> 02:24:30,521
The one they caught.

2002
02:24:31,562 --> 02:24:33,229
Ajmal Kasab...

2003
02:24:36,021 --> 02:24:38,062
I'm the one who put a gun in his hands.

2004
02:24:43,729 --> 02:24:48,187
They walked straight...

2005
02:24:50,562 --> 02:24:52,687
into my home in broad daylight!

2006
02:24:58,437 --> 02:24:59,437
Iqbal,

2007
02:25:00,812 --> 02:25:01,687
Khanani,

2008
02:25:02,687 --> 02:25:03,771
Mir,

2009
02:25:04,396 --> 02:25:05,479
Bhuttovi.

2010
02:25:06,396 --> 02:25:08,146
I'll finish every last one of them.

2011
02:25:09,562 --> 02:25:11,979
Revenge burns hot, Hamza.

2012
02:25:12,437 --> 02:25:13,728
It'll torch your neighbor's house,

2013
02:25:13,729 --> 02:25:16,021
but the flames will always cross
your own courtyard.

2014
02:25:16,771 --> 02:25:19,979
One wrong move and you go down.

2015
02:25:20,687 --> 02:25:23,812
If even one of our assets gets
caught across the border,

2016
02:25:25,646 --> 02:25:28,812
India's reputation will crumble into dust.

2017
02:25:32,146 --> 02:25:33,896
You'll get your revenge.

2018
02:25:38,146 --> 02:25:39,062
Be patient.

2019
02:25:41,312 --> 02:25:43,271
We're in this game to win.

2020
02:25:44,187 --> 02:25:46,604
And to win, there's only one rule...

2021
02:25:46,937 --> 02:25:48,354
For us to stay alive.

2022
02:25:54,812 --> 02:25:55,729
Here...

2023
02:26:16,646 --> 02:26:17,812
A wounded lion doesn't fear death.

2024
02:26:19,812 --> 02:26:21,229
It just makes him more lethal.

2025
02:26:43,396 --> 02:26:44,396
Where were you all night?

2026
02:26:46,021 --> 02:26:46,937
Where were you?!

2027
02:26:48,562 --> 02:26:51,479
I'm sick of waiting for you
in this pigeonhole!

2028
02:26:53,937 --> 02:26:55,478
Hamza, I'm talking to you!
Answer me!

2029
02:26:55,479 --> 02:26:57,604
I left my father's home for you!

2030
02:27:02,229 --> 02:27:03,271
Are you drunk?

2031
02:27:04,729 --> 02:27:05,729
Who were you with?

2032
02:27:07,354 --> 02:27:08,396
Some girl?

2033
02:27:10,312 --> 02:27:11,562
Were you with her all night?

2034
02:27:14,062 --> 02:27:15,270
Hamza, answer me!

2035
02:27:15,271 --> 02:27:17,479
Did you spend the night with her?
Who is she?

2036
02:27:17,979 --> 02:27:19,811
Who is she?
Who were you with, Hamza?

2037
02:27:19,812 --> 02:27:20,896
Answer me!

2038
02:27:53,271 --> 02:27:56,271
I want to be the undisputed king
of Karachi.

2039
02:27:58,812 --> 02:27:59,895
If you can walk beside me,

2040
02:27:59,896 --> 02:28:02,437
you'll have every right to me
as long as I live.

2041
02:28:04,104 --> 02:28:05,354
But hereafter...

2042
02:28:06,729 --> 02:28:08,437
there will be no more questions.

2043
02:28:11,021 --> 02:28:11,979
If you can't do that,

2044
02:28:13,854 --> 02:28:15,354
the door's right there.

2045
02:29:16,812 --> 02:29:17,771
Hereafter,

2046
02:29:18,687 --> 02:29:21,396
if you ever ask me to leave again,

2047
02:29:24,437 --> 02:29:26,562
I'll burn you alive in your sleep.

2048
02:29:42,896 --> 02:29:44,186
PEOPLE'S DECISION
PAKISTAN AWAMI PARTY

2049
02:29:44,187 --> 02:29:46,354
My brothers of Lyari,

2050
02:29:47,396 --> 02:29:49,604
seeing this kind of energy today,

2051
02:29:50,229 --> 02:29:55,521
my late wife Benazir's soul
must be smiling.

2052
02:29:59,479 --> 02:30:03,104
Our opposition may have forgotten,

2053
02:30:03,271 --> 02:30:04,854
but once upon a time,

2054
02:30:05,229 --> 02:30:07,354
Lyari voted for me too,

2055
02:30:07,521 --> 02:30:10,561
just like you voted for Jameel sahab,

2056
02:30:10,562 --> 02:30:13,187
and made me the MNA
